1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,200
Hello English learners, welcome back to EnglishPod.
英语学习者你们好，欢迎回到EnglishPod。

2
00:00:04,200 --> 00:00:05,200
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:06,200
And I'm Erika.
我是Erika。

4
00:00:06,200 --> 00:00:11,360
Today we're bringing you a lesson about the office, so something related to business,
今天我们带来一节关于办公室的课程，所以跟商务有关，

5
00:00:11,360 --> 00:00:12,360
right?
对吧？

6
00:00:12,360 --> 00:00:13,360
That's right.
没错。

7
00:00:13,360 --> 00:00:18,880
And in this lesson, we're learning language you can use to tell someone they did a good
在这节课中，我们将学习一些可以用来告诉别人他们做得好的语言，

8
00:00:18,880 --> 00:00:19,880
job.
工作。

9
00:00:19,880 --> 00:00:21,680
Okay, so a job well done.
好的，所以是工作做得好。

10
00:00:21,680 --> 00:00:24,120
You want to praise somebody.
你想表扬某人。

11
00:00:24,120 --> 00:00:25,120
That's right.
没错。

12
00:00:25,120 --> 00:00:30,520
And we're going to listen in as a manager praises his employee on a presentation.
我们将听一段经理表扬员工在演示中的表现。

13
00:00:30,520 --> 00:00:36,120
Okay, so before we listen to the dialogue, let's take a look very quickly at vocabulary
好的，所以在听对话之前，我们先快速看一下词汇，

14
00:00:36,120 --> 00:00:38,780
preview.
预览。

15
00:00:38,780 --> 00:00:39,780
Vocabulary preview.
词汇预览。

16
00:00:39,780 --> 00:00:44,360
Well, we're going to hear both of these words in the dialogue.
嗯，我们会在对话中听到这两个词。

17
00:00:44,360 --> 00:00:47,200
And the first one is a whiz.
第一个是“a whiz”。

18
00:00:47,200 --> 00:00:48,280
Whiz.
“Whiz”。

19
00:00:48,280 --> 00:00:49,280
To be a whiz.
“To be a whiz”。

20
00:00:49,280 --> 00:00:51,060
Okay, so it's an adjective.
好的，所以它是一个形容词。

21
00:00:51,060 --> 00:00:52,480
Somebody is a whiz.
某人是“a whiz”。

22
00:00:52,480 --> 00:00:53,480
That's right.
没错。

23
00:00:53,480 --> 00:00:55,800
And the whiz comes from the word wizard.
“Whiz”这个词来自“wizard”。

24
00:00:55,800 --> 00:01:00,120
Okay, so kind of like a, like a witch, but a guy witch.
好的，有点像女巫，但是男巫。

25
00:01:00,120 --> 00:01:01,120
Yeah, man witch.
是的，男巫。

26
00:01:01,120 --> 00:01:05,800
But so a whiz is someone who is really good at something.
但是“a whiz”是指某人在某方面非常擅长。

27
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:10,960
Okay, so I can say David is a computer whiz.
好的，所以我可以这样说：David是个电脑高手。

28
00:01:10,960 --> 00:01:13,280
Or Anthony is a math whiz.
或者Anthony是个数学天才。

29
00:01:13,280 --> 00:01:17,860
Okay, so he's really good at computers or he's really good at math or he knows a lot
好的，所以他在电脑方面很擅长，或者他在数学方面很擅长，或者他对数学了解很多，

30
00:01:17,860 --> 00:01:18,860
about math.
数学。

31
00:01:18,860 --> 00:01:19,860
Exactly.
没错。

32
00:01:19,860 --> 00:01:20,860
Okay.
好的。

33
00:01:20,860 --> 00:01:21,860
And our second word.
我们的第二个词。

34
00:01:21,860 --> 00:01:23,920
Well, we're going to hear about slides.
嗯，我们会听到关于“slides”。

35
00:01:23,920 --> 00:01:24,920
Slides.
“Slides”。

36
00:01:24,920 --> 00:01:26,680
PowerPoint slides.
“PowerPoint slides”。

37
00:01:26,680 --> 00:01:27,680
PowerPoint slides.
“PowerPoint slides”。

38
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:30,800
Okay, so everyone knows PowerPoint, right?
好的，大家都知道PowerPoint，对吧？

39
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:31,800
A computer program.
一个电脑程序。

40
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:36,280
A computer program that you use to make presentations.
一个用来做演示的电脑程序。

41
00:01:36,280 --> 00:01:40,000
And a slide is one page in that presentation.
而“slide”是那个演示中的一页。

42
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:46,680
Okay, so if you have 10 pages in your PowerPoint presentation, you basically have 10 slides.
好的，所以如果你的PowerPoint演示有10页，你基本上就有10张幻灯片。

43
00:01:46,680 --> 00:01:47,680
Exactly.
没错。

44
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:48,680
Very good.
非常好。

45
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:53,640
So now let's listen to the dialogue for the first time and we're going to see what's happening
所以现在让我们第一次听对话，看看这次商务会议上发生了什么，

46
00:01:53,640 --> 00:01:59,040
in this business meeting.
会议。

47
00:01:59,040 --> 00:02:03,400
And so that concludes my outline for our marketing strategy next year.
那么，这就是我对明年营销策略的概述。

48
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:06,120
Thank you very much for your time.
非常感谢你们的时间。

49
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:10,760
Hey, that was quite the presentation.
嘿，这真是一场精彩的演示。

50
00:02:10,760 --> 00:02:14,640
Honestly, I was completely blown away by your strategy outline.
老实说，你的策略概述让我完全震撼了。

51
00:02:14,640 --> 00:02:18,240
I've got to say, Alex, you really wowed me today.
我得说，Alex，你今天真的让我惊叹。

52
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:19,800
Come on, it was nothing.
别这么说，这没什么。

53
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:21,600
I'm just doing my job.
我只是在做我的工作。

54
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:24,200
No, I think you deserve some recognition here.
不，我认为你在这里值得一些认可。

55
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:29,000
I mean, if I look back on your previous presentations, this is a huge improvement.
我的意思是，如果回顾你之前的演示，这次进步巨大。

56
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:31,600
Well, Christian did give me a hand with the slides.
嗯，Kirsten确实帮了我一把，处理幻灯片。

57
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:33,400
She's a real whiz on PowerPoint.
她在PowerPoint上真是个高手。

58
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:37,080
And I saw that you took on board my feedback about pricing strategies.
我看到你采纳了我关于定价策略的反馈。

59
00:02:37,080 --> 00:02:40,160
I really appreciate you taking the time to think through my suggestions.
我真的很感激你花时间思考我的建议。

60
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:44,980
Yeah, well, that was some good advice.
是啊，那是一些好建议。

61
00:02:44,980 --> 00:02:46,560
You made some really good points.
你提出了一些很好的观点。

62
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:49,360
Well, I just wanted to say, well done.
嗯，我只想说，干得好。

63
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:51,960
Really, you did a great job.
真的，你做得很好。

64
00:02:51,960 --> 00:03:00,760
All right, well, it sounds like the employee is a little bit shy or embarrassed by receiving
好的，听起来这个员工有点害羞，或者因为收到这么多赞美而感到尴尬，

65
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:01,760
all of these compliments.
赞美。

66
00:03:01,760 --> 00:03:05,640
Yeah, I guess he's kind of being humble about it.
是的，我想他有点谦虚。

67
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:06,640
Exactly.
没错。

68
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:08,720
So why don't we move on to the language now?
那我们为什么不现在进入语言部分呢？

69
00:03:08,720 --> 00:03:13,200
There are so many really useful phrases in this dialogue that I think we're just going
这个对话中有很多非常有用的短语，我想我们今天，

70
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:14,800
to focus on those today.
就专注于这些。

71
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:19,080
So let's get started with Fluency Builder.
那么让我们开始流利度构建。

72
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:20,080
Fluency Builder.
流利度构建。

73
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:24,400
Okay, so today on Fluency Builder, let's start with our first phrase.
好的，今天在流利度构建中，让我们从第一个短语开始。

74
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:31,480
The boss was so impressed with the presentation that he said, I was completely blown away.
老板对演示印象非常深刻，他说：“我完全被震撼了。”

75
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:33,920
To be completely blown away.
“To be completely blown away”。

76
00:03:33,920 --> 00:03:37,680
Okay, so to be completely blown away.
好的，所以是“to be completely blown away”。

77
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:39,360
Or to be blown away.
或者“to be blown away”。

78
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:43,480
All right, so what does that mean, to be blown away?
好的，那么“to be blown away”是什么意思？

79
00:03:43,480 --> 00:03:48,000
To be surprised and amazed, but in a very positive way.
感到惊讶和惊叹，但以非常积极的方式。

80
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:54,040
Okay, so I can say, I'm surprised, I'm amazed, but I'm still not very clear on this.
好的，所以我可以说我感到惊讶、惊叹，但我还是不太清楚。

81
00:03:54,040 --> 00:03:59,200
Why don't we listen to a couple of examples of how we could use this phrase?
我们为什么不听几个例子，看看如何使用这个短语？

82
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:02,320
Example one.
例子一。

83
00:04:02,320 --> 00:04:07,720
Carl blew me away with his knowledge of political science.
Carl的政治学知识让我惊叹。

84
00:04:07,720 --> 00:04:10,360
Example two.
例子二。

85
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:13,520
I was blown away when I heard that Jenny and Rick had gotten married.
当我听说Jenny和Rick结婚时，我完全震惊了。

86
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:17,680
They've known each other for less than a month.
他们认识还不到一个月。

87
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:20,880
Example three.
例子三。

88
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:24,680
My parents were blown away when they found out I had a tattoo.
我父母发现我有纹身时，完全震惊了。

89
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:27,640
Okay, so I think that's a little bit clearer now.
好的，所以我想现在更清楚一点了。

90
00:04:27,640 --> 00:04:32,600
And this is a wonderful way to give your praise to someone when they do something really
这是一个很好的方式，当某人做了非常出色的事情时，给予他们表扬，

91
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:33,600
amazing.
事情。

92
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:35,680
Okay, so completely blown away.
好的，所以“completely blown away”。

93
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:37,000
You blew me away.
“You blew me away”。

94
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,000
That's right.
没错。

95
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,320
Now, what about our second word?
那么我们的第二个词呢？

96
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:41,000
Well, it's quite similar.
嗯，它很相似。

97
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:44,980
The boss said that you really wowed me.
老板说：“你确实让我惊叹。”

98
00:04:44,980 --> 00:04:46,040
You wowed me.
“You wowed me”。

99
00:04:46,040 --> 00:04:47,360
To wow someone.
“To wow someone”。

100
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:50,680
Okay, so it's spelled W-O-W, wow.
好的，它拼写为W-O-W，wow。

101
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:54,160
So when you wow someone, you make that person go, wow.
所以当你让某人惊叹时，你让那个人发出“哇”的感叹。

102
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:56,120
Okay, so you impress somebody.
好的，所以你给某人留下深刻印象。

103
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:57,120
Yep.
是的。

104
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:58,120
To wow someone.
“To wow someone”。

105
00:04:58,120 --> 00:04:59,120
I can use it as a verb.
我可以把它用作动词。

106
00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:00,240
You wowed me.
“You wowed me”。

107
00:05:00,240 --> 00:05:01,600
I want to wow you.
“I want to wow you”。

108
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:03,400
Well, I want you to wow me.
嗯，“I want you to wow me”。

109
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:05,280
Okay, so wow.
好的，所以是“wow”。

110
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:07,660
Now let's take a look at our third phrase.
现在让我们看看第三个短语。

111
00:05:07,660 --> 00:05:09,440
The guy, he's a little bit shy.
这个人有点害羞。

112
00:05:09,440 --> 00:05:13,660
He's trying to be a little bit humble about, you know, receiving so many compliments.
他试图在收到这么多赞美时表现得谦虚一点，

113
00:05:13,660 --> 00:05:16,080
So he says, oh, it was nothing.
赞美。

114
00:05:16,080 --> 00:05:17,080
It was nothing.
所以他说：“哦，这没什么。”

115
00:05:17,080 --> 00:05:18,080
Really?
“It was nothing”。

116
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:19,080
It was nothing.
真的吗？

117
00:05:19,080 --> 00:05:20,080
It was nothing.
“It was nothing”。

118
00:05:20,080 --> 00:05:22,820
So that's a way of saying it wasn't hard or it's not a big deal.
“It was nothing”。

119
00:05:22,820 --> 00:05:23,820
It's not that important.
所以这是一种说“这并不难”或“没什么大不了的”的方式。

120
00:05:23,820 --> 00:05:24,820
Exactly.
没那么重要。

121
00:05:24,820 --> 00:05:28,720
So if somebody's saying, wow, thank you so much for lending me your car, don't worry
没错。

122
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:29,720
about it.
所以如果有人对你说：“哇，非常感谢你借给我你的车，别担心。”

123
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:30,720
It was nothing.
别担心。

124
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:31,720
It was nothing.
“It was nothing”。

125
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:32,720
All right.
“It was nothing”。

126
00:05:32,720 --> 00:05:34,800
It's a polite way actually to respond to a nice compliment.
好的。

127
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:35,800
Very good.
实际上，这是一种回应善意赞美的礼貌方式。

128
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:40,360
So before we move on to our next phrase, let's listen to a couple of examples with it was
非常好。

129
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:42,560
nothing.
所以在进入下一个短语之前，让我们听几个关于“it was nothing”的例子，

130
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:43,560
Example one.
例子。

131
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:45,960
Thanks for lending me your car this week.
例子一。

132
00:05:45,960 --> 00:05:47,720
I really appreciate it.
谢谢你本周借给我你的车。

133
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:48,800
It's okay, really.
我真的很感激。

134
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:51,360
It was nothing.
没关系，真的。

135
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:53,800
Example two.
“It was nothing”。

136
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:56,840
I can't believe you organized the surprise birthday party.
例子二。

137
00:05:56,840 --> 00:05:58,200
Thank you so much.
我简直不敢相信你组织了惊喜生日派对。

138
00:05:58,200 --> 00:05:59,200
Don't worry about it.
非常感谢你。

139
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:00,200
It was nothing.
别担心。

140
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:01,200
Okay.
“It was nothing”。

141
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:04,280
So I think that's pretty clear.
好的。

142
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:10,520
Now our final phrase here for fluency builder, the employee said that Kirsten gave him a
所以我想这很清楚。

143
00:06:10,520 --> 00:06:11,520
hand.
现在，流利度构建中的最后一个短语，员工说Kirsten帮了他一把，

144
00:06:11,520 --> 00:06:12,520
Okay.
一把。

145
00:06:12,520 --> 00:06:14,480
So to give someone a hand.
好的。

146
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:15,480
Give me a hand.
所以是“to give someone a hand”。

147
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:17,080
Give me a hand.
“Give me a hand”。

148
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:18,200
Basically to help someone.
“Give me a hand”。

149
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:20,000
Help me or assist me.
基本上就是帮助某人。

150
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,000
Okay.
帮助我或协助我。

151
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:24,880
So to help someone, give me a hand or let me give you a hand.
好的。

152
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:25,880
That's right.
所以是帮助某人，“give me a hand”或“let me give you a hand”。

153
00:06:25,880 --> 00:06:26,880
All right.
没错。

154
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:27,880
Very good.
好的。

155
00:06:27,880 --> 00:06:29,360
So great phrases in fluency builder today.
非常好。

156
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:33,560
I think it's time for us to listen to the dialogue for the second time.
所以今天流利度构建中有很棒的短语。

157
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:37,600
We're going to slow it down a little bit so we can catch all these phrases and then we'll
我想是时候第二次听对话了。

158
