come back.
我们会放慢一点速度，这样我们就能抓住所有这些短语，然后我们再回来，

159
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:49,920
And so that concludes my outline for our marketing strategy for next year.
回来。

160
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:52,320
Thank you very much for your time.
那么，这就是我对明年营销策略的概述。

161
00:06:52,320 --> 00:06:55,520
Hey, that was quite the presentation.
非常感谢你们的时间。

162
00:06:55,520 --> 00:07:00,680
Honestly, I was completely blown away by your strategy outline.
嘿，这真是一场精彩的演示。

163
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:05,000
I've got to say, Alex, you really wowed me today.
老实说，你的策略概述让我完全震撼了。

164
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:06,920
Ah, come on.
我得说，Alex，你今天真的让我惊叹。

165
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:07,920
It was nothing.
啊，别这么说。

166
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:10,000
I'm just doing my job.
这没什么。

167
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:13,680
No, I think you deserve some recognition here.
我只是在做我的工作。

168
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:19,880
I mean, if I look back on your previous presentations, this is a huge improvement.
不，我认为你在这里值得一些认可。

169
00:07:19,880 --> 00:07:23,680
Well, Kirsten did give me a hand with the slides.
我的意思是，如果回顾你之前的演示，这次进步巨大。

170
00:07:23,680 --> 00:07:26,200
She's a real whiz on PowerPoint.
嗯，Kirsten确实帮了我一把，处理幻灯片。

171
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:31,280
And I saw that you took on board my feedback about pricing strategies.
她在PowerPoint上真是个高手。

172
00:07:31,280 --> 00:07:35,360
I really appreciate you taking the time to think through my suggestions.
我看到你采纳了我关于定价策略的反馈。

173
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:38,960
Yeah, well, that was some good advice.
我真的很感激你花时间思考我的建议。

174
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:41,120
You made some really good points.
是啊，那是一些好建议。

175
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:44,800
Well, I just wanted to say, well done.
你提出了一些很好的观点。

176
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:47,640
Really, you did a great job.
嗯，我只想说，干得好。

177
00:07:47,640 --> 00:07:55,920
Okay, so like we said before, there's a lot of really helpful phrases in here.
真的，你做得很好。

178
00:07:55,920 --> 00:08:01,840
And we're going to look at a few more of these in Putting It Together.
好的，就像我们之前说的，这里有很多非常有用的短语。

179
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:03,440
Putting It Together.
我们将在“Putting It Together”中再看几个。

180
00:08:03,440 --> 00:08:07,360
Okay, so let's start with the first phrase.
“Putting It Together”。

181
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:13,320
The boss was quite impressed with him and he said, that was quite the presentation.
好的，让我们从第一个短语开始。

182
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:14,600
That was quite the presentation.
老板对他印象深刻，他说：“那真是一场精彩的演示。”

183
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:17,520
All right, quite the presentation.
“That was quite the presentation”。

184
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:22,720
So this phrase, quite the presentation, it means it was good, right?
好的，“quite the presentation”。

185
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:23,720
It was special.
所以这个短语“quite the presentation”，意思是它很好，对吧？

186
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:25,000
It was very good.
它很特别。

187
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:30,440
Yep, now we can take the noun presentation out and replace it with any other noun.
它非常好。

188
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:35,800
All right, so I can say, Bob is quite the basketball player.
是的，现在我们可以把名词“presentation”拿出来，用任何其他名词替换。

189
00:08:35,800 --> 00:08:39,760
Why don't we listen now for a few more examples?
好的，所以我可以这样说：Bob是个相当不错的篮球运动员。

190
00:08:39,760 --> 00:08:42,360
Example one.
我们现在为什么不听几个更多的例子？

191
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:44,120
I heard you are quite the dancer.
例子一。

192
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:48,120
Can you teach me some moves?
我听说你舞跳得相当好。

193
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:51,000
Example two.
你能教我一些动作吗？

194
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,520
Carl is quite the ladies' man.
例子二。

195
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:57,080
He is very good when it comes to talking to girls.
Carl是个相当有女人缘的人。

196
00:08:57,080 --> 00:09:00,200
Example three.
他在和女孩聊天方面很擅长。

197
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:02,360
Nancy is quite gifted at math.
例子三。

198
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:06,740
She can solve any math problem you give her.
Nancy在数学方面相当有天赋。

199
00:09:06,740 --> 00:09:11,200
So you're saying in a very good way that something is very good.
她能解决你给她的任何数学问题。

200
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:12,200
Or special.
所以你是以一种非常好的方式说某件事非常好，或者很特别。

201
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,200
Very special.
非常特别。

202
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:18,000
All right, so the boss was very impressed with the employee and he said, and I saw that
好的，老板对员工印象深刻，他说，我注意到

203
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:21,000
you took on board my feedback.
你采纳了我的反馈。

204
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:23,320
To take on board my feedback.
采纳我的反馈。

205
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:26,840
Okay, so take on board something.
好的，所以“采纳某物”。

206
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:31,160
So here, my feedback is my suggestions, right?
这里，我的反馈就是我的建议，对吧？

207
00:09:31,160 --> 00:09:37,640
And when you take on board my feedback, you accept my feedback and you use it.
当你采纳我的反馈时，你接受我的反馈并加以运用。

208
00:09:37,640 --> 00:09:45,040
Okay, so I can say, for example, I want you to take on board my ideas.
好的，所以我可以举例说，我希望你采纳我的想法。

209
00:09:45,040 --> 00:09:48,240
Or Jenny took on board a few of my suggestions.
或者珍妮采纳了我的一些建议。

210
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:49,400
I was really happy.
我真的很高兴。

211
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:50,640
Okay, very good.
好的，非常好。

212
00:09:50,640 --> 00:09:52,840
So to take on board, to accept and use.
所以“采纳”，就是接受并运用。

213
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:58,040
All right, so take on board feedback, take on board suggestion, take on board ideas.
好的，所以采纳反馈、采纳建议、采纳想法。

214
00:09:58,040 --> 00:09:59,800
Okay, very good.
好的，非常好。

215
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:02,840
And we have one more phrase, I'm putting it together today.
我们还有一个短语，我今天把它整合起来。

216
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:05,120
To think something through.
仔细考虑某事。

217
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:06,520
To think it through.
仔细考虑它。

218
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:09,320
Okay, so think it through.
好的，所以仔细考虑。

219
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:14,560
So here, the boss said that he took the time to think through my suggestions.
这里，老板说他花时间仔细考虑了我的建议。

220
00:10:14,560 --> 00:10:16,680
So think through, what does that mean?
所以“仔细考虑”，这是什么意思？

221
00:10:16,680 --> 00:10:20,680
To think carefully about all of the details of something.
仔细考虑某事的全部细节。

222
00:10:20,680 --> 00:10:24,520
Okay, so to take into consideration all the aspects.
好的，就是考虑到所有方面。

223
00:10:24,520 --> 00:10:28,280
Right, so why don't we give an example?
对，那我们为什么不举个例子呢？

224
00:10:28,280 --> 00:10:30,840
If you're thinking through a plan, right?
如果你在仔细考虑一个计划，对吧？

225
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:33,800
You don't just think about the end, the outcome.
你不只是考虑最终结果。

226
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:38,280
You want to think about all of the small details, the steps in that plan.
你要考虑所有的小细节，计划中的步骤。

227
00:10:38,280 --> 00:10:42,440
Okay, so maybe I want to buy a new car, but it's a lot of money.
好的，也许我想买一辆新车，但花很多钱。

228
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:44,800
So I really have to think it through.
所以我真的得仔细考虑。

229
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:50,240
So you have to think carefully about everything that is involved in buying the new car.
所以你必须仔细考虑买新车涉及的一切。

230
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:54,360
All the money you're going to have to, you know, not spend on parties.
所有你不得不省下的钱，比如不花在派对上。

231
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:56,120
Exactly, you have to think it through.
没错，你必须仔细考虑。

232
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:58,720
You have to analyze it very carefully.
你必须非常仔细地分析。

233
00:10:58,720 --> 00:10:59,720
That's right.
没错。

234
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:01,920
So let's give a few examples of how we can use this phrase.
那我们举几个例子，看看怎么用这个短语。

235
00:11:01,920 --> 00:11:05,480
Hey, Marco, have you thought through my suggestions?
嘿，马可，你仔细考虑过我的建议了吗？

236
00:11:05,480 --> 00:11:07,040
I can say, you guys are very young.
我可以说，你们还太年轻。

237
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:09,600
I think you should think it through before you get married.
我觉得你们结婚前应该仔细考虑。

238
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:10,600
Good advice.
好建议。

239
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:12,480
Okay, so to think it through.
好的，所以“仔细考虑”。

240
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:22,920
Okay, so three great phrases and why don't we hear them one more time in our dialogue.
好的，三个很棒的短语，我们为什么不在对话里再听一遍呢？

241
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:27,280
And so that concludes my outline for our marketing strategy next year.
这就是我明年营销策略的概要。

242
00:11:27,280 --> 00:11:30,280
Thank you very much for your time.
非常感谢您的时间。

243
00:11:30,280 --> 00:11:34,600
Hey, that was quite the presentation.
嘿，那真是个精彩的演示。

244
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:38,520
Honestly, I was completely blown away by your strategy outline.
说实话，你的策略大纲完全让我惊艳。

245
00:11:38,520 --> 00:11:42,120
I've got to say, Alex, you really wowed me today.
我得说，亚历克斯，你今天真的让我印象深刻。

246
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:43,680
Come on, it was nothing.
别这么说，没什么。

247
00:11:43,680 --> 00:11:45,480
I'm just doing my job.
我只是做好本职工作。

248
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:48,080
No, I think you deserve some recognition here.
不，我觉得你值得表扬。

249
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:52,960
I mean, if I look back on your previous presentations, this is a huge improvement.
我是说，回顾你之前的演示，这次进步巨大。

250
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:55,480
Well, Christian did give me a hand with the slides.
嗯，克里斯蒂安帮我做了幻灯片。

251
00:11:55,480 --> 00:11:57,240
She's a real whiz on PowerPoint.
她真是个PPT高手。

252
00:11:57,240 --> 00:12:00,920
And I saw that you took on board my feedback about pricing strategies.
我注意到你采纳了我关于定价策略的反馈。

253
00:12:00,920 --> 00:12:04,000
I really appreciate you taking the time to think through my suggestions.
我真的很感激你花时间仔细考虑我的建议。

254
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:08,840
Yeah, well, that was some good advice.
是啊，那些建议不错。

255
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:10,440
You made some really good points.
你提出了一些很好的观点。

256
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:13,240
Well, I just wanted to say, well done.
嗯，我只想说，干得好。

257
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:16,640
Really, you did a great job.
真的，你做得很好。

258
00:12:16,640 --> 00:12:25,560
Okay, great dialogue and some interesting phrases for giving praise, right?
好的，很棒的对话，还有一些有趣的表扬短语，对吧？

259
00:12:25,560 --> 00:12:28,000
That's, I think, very important in the workplace.
我觉得这在职场中非常重要。

260
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:34,280
Yeah, and you know what, I read recently that something like six out of every ten employees
是啊，你知道吗，我最近读到，大约每十个员工中有六个

261
00:12:34,280 --> 00:12:37,320
don't get regular praise from their boss.
得不到老板的定期表扬。

262
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:38,320
It's very important.
这非常重要。

263
00:12:38,320 --> 00:12:44,360
And in some cultures, well, it's not very common to praise or to give positive feedback
在某些文化中，表扬或给予积极反馈给员工

264
00:12:44,360 --> 00:12:45,360
to their employees.
并不常见。

265
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:51,200
Yeah, but I think for Western employees, actually, it's really important and it helps them work
是啊，但我认为对西方员工来说，这真的很重要，而且他们听到“干得好”的次数越多，

266
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:55,600
harder the more times they hear, job well done.
工作就越努力。

267
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:56,760
Yeah, very good.
是的，非常好。

268
00:12:56,760 --> 00:13:01,360
So now you have the tools that maybe you can use with your employees or...
所以现在你有了工具，也许可以用在你的员工身上，或者...

269
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:02,360
With your friends.
用在朋友身上。

270
00:13:02,360 --> 00:13:03,360
With your friends.
用在朋友身上。

271
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:04,360
Yep.
是的。

272
00:13:04,360 --> 00:13:07,560
Okay, so if you have any questions, comments, or doubts, please come to our website, EnglishPod.com.
好的，如果你有任何问题、评论或疑问，请访问我们的网站EnglishPod.com。

273
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:10,960
Yep, Marco and I are always around to help you out.
是的，马可和我随时都在帮你。

274
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:14,960
So until next time, thanks for listening and goodbye.
那么下次再见，感谢收听，再见。

275
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:15,960
Bye.
再见。

276
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:45,340
Happy Marketing University of Florida.
佛罗里达大学营销快乐。
